According to him, the new Suez Canal constituted an infrastructure that could balance the physical, technological, human and financial capital, as it was a work carried out in a record time of 12 months against 36 months, as previously planned. 
To the minister, who was accompanied by the ambassador of Angola to Egypt, António da Costa Fernandes, the project dignifies the government of Egypt and the African continent. 
Profits generated through the Suez Canal are about five billion US dollars, but the investment calculations go up to 15 billion dollars, three times more after these works, until 2023. 
The Suez Canal extends from the city of Suez in Egypt on the shores of the Red Sea to Port Said on the shores of the Mediterranean Sea, and has 163 kilometers in length - the largest channel in the world (from this extension, 50 km were excavated in desert). Egypt
